<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-10271] Performance regression while fetching a key from a single partition</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-10271</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is follow-up bug for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-10030&quot; title=&quot;Throw exception while fetching a key from a single partition&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-10030&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-10030&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;StreamThreadStateStoreProvider excessive loop over calling internalTopologyBuilder.topicGroups(), which is synchronized, thus causing significant performance degradation to the caller, especially when store has many partitions.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
